562066, "name": "Malay Music", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/Malay_Music?f_ri=562066", "nofollow": false}]}, {"id": 44565741, "title": "THE PAST MUSICAL IDENTITY OF MALAY WORLD", "created_at": "2020-11-24T05:33:55.534-08:00", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/44565741/THE_PAST_MUSICAL_IDENTITY_OF_MALAY_WORLD?f_ri=562066", "dom_id": "work_44565741", "summary": "Malay literary works provide songs and musical imagery as illustrations of musical life in the period in which they were writing. Song reference is a literary device used to record musical events that were part of the narrative of a particular event in Malay classical literature. Song imagery, mostly short, is a literary technique used to embellish narrative flow and the literary appeal of a prose or verse form in Malay literary texts. The objective of this study is to provide the past song forms from twelve literary works dating from the late fourteenth century to the late nineteenth century to illustrate the past musical of the Malay world. This qualitative study referred to sources from Malay Concordance Project (MCP) in which presented pre-modern Malay written texts. From this study, there were fifteen song forms and they were associated with celebrations and festival. Some song forms were also accompanied by specific musical instruments.", "downloadable_attachments": [{"id": 65020263, "asset_id": 44565741, "asset_type": "Work", "always_allow_download": false}], "ordered_authors": [{"id": 4440883, "first_name": "Shafa'atussara", "last_name": "Silahudin", "domain_name": "universitimalaya", "page_name": "ShafaatussaraSilahudin", "display_name": "Shafa'atussara Silahudin", "profile_url": "https://universitimalaya.academia.edu/ShafaatussaraSilahudin?f_ri=562066", "photo": "https://0.academia-photos.com/4440883/1812719/32741462/s65_shafa_atussara.silahudin.jpg"}], "research_interests": [{"id": 13850, "name": "Malay World", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/Malay_World?f_ri=562066", "n